data.description: Stopping human trafficking is a priority in Maryland, where 72 cases were reported last year, according to the National Human Trafficking Hotline. That’s why this summer, Gov. Larry Hogan announced a series of initiatives to combat it, including the creation of my position.
data.title: Ending human trafficking a priority in Md.
